The paper discusses the classification of texts using complex networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper focuses on the semantic and syntactic features of texts. The second most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as text classification is an essential task in information retrieval. The third most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the use of metrics and algorithms to classify texts. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper employs complex networks to represent texts. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the use of machine translation and authorship recognition, which are applications of AI.
